The paper focuses on modelling physical properties of everyday objects for autonomous robots, specifically for safe and fast navigation of mobile robots carrying payloads over different obstacles and floor materials. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses RGB-D images and generative adversarial networks (GANs) to predict body deformations, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The use of GANs also suggests that the paper may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
